"n.警长，县治安官 【英】 n.县治安官(an important official of a shire or county charged primarily with judicial duties) 【考】 understudy : star / deputy : sheriff(替补演员和名角/代 理长官和长官) n. (主要负责司法事务的)治安官 【记】sheriff = stiff(adj 僵硬的), 治安官的特点是僵硬的. 【类】understudy: star = deputy: sheriff替补演员替补名角 = 代理长官替补长官 【记】sheriff就是当地shire 郡的shepherd 牧羊人 sheriff (n.)  late Old English scirgerefa ""representative of royal authority in a shire,"" from scir (see shire) + gerefa ""chief, official, reeve"" (see reeve). As an American county official, attested from 1660s; sheriff's sale first recorded 1798. Sheriff's tooth (late 14c.) was a common name for the annual tax levied to pay for the sheriff's victuals during court sessions."
